This paper deals with clustering algorithms, which are commonly used in machine learning and data analysis. The paper proposes a new method for determining the number of clusters, which is a common problem in clustering. This method is applicable to a wide range of clustering algorithms, including Gaussian mixtures and Spectral Clustering, which are commonly used in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.ST (Statistics).
